Pre-Game Insights: Guinea Bissau national football team are in second place with five points.
Egypt are the runaway leader of the group with nine points.
Mahmoud Trezeguet is expected to lead the frontline of the host nation.
Mahmoud Trezeguet scored a brace of goals last game against Burkina Faso.
The hosts have not won any of their last five games in all competitions.
Egypt have had a mixed result in that period, winning two, losing two and drawing once.
The away side currently holds a four-point lead over Guinea Bissau in Group A.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kick-Off: Monday, 10 June 2024 at 9:30 PM IST
Others: Houboulang Mendes is back and available post-suspension.
Mohamed Salah is the star of the Egypt side, having netted four goals in the World Cup qualifiers.
